OL,3,CPioneering treatment could save sight
OL,4,Cof chemical attack victims
OL,6,FPioneering treatment which could save
OL,7,Fthe sight of victims of corrosive
OL,8,Fchemical attacks is being developed by
OL,9,Fscientists in the North East.
OL,11,FA team from Newcastle University is
OL,12,Fworking on the enzyme treatment which
OL,13,Fcan stop the damaging effects of
OL,14,Falkaline on eyes.
OL,16,FThe use of chemicals as a weapon is a
OL,17,Fcrime which appears to be on the rise
OL,18,Fin England and Wales - and has been
OL,19,Fblighting the North East in recent
OL,20,Fyears.
