OL,3,CPioneering treatment could save sight
OL,4,Cof chemical attack victims
OL,6,FThey say this kills off or alters
OL,7,Fvital stem cells that exist to help
OL,8,Fmaintain the surface of the eye.
OL,10,FClinical trials are now underway of a
OL,11,Ftechnique to treat the stiffened area
OL,12,Fwith an enzyme that restores the
OL,13,Foriginal softness, helping maintain
OL,14,Fthe stem cells and allowing them to
OL,15,Fstimulate healing.
OL,17,F"One of the benefits of this treatment
OL,18,Fis that it's not a stem cell therapy,"
OL,19,Fcontinued Professor Connon.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/6
